This paper deals with the problem of scheduling tasks for a human operator, taking into account the operator's past utilization and the Yerkes-Dodson law. This problem is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and cybernetics (cs.CY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
